headline: Cboe Global Markets Announces Departure of Global President Dave Howson
summary: Cboe Global Markets, Inc. (Cboe: CBOE), the world's leading derivatives and securities exchange network, today announced that Dave Howson, Executive Vice President and Global President, will be stepping down from the role effective August 1, 2025. Howson will be returning home to the UK after spending three years in Chicago in his role as Global President.

headline: Zacks Industry Outlook Highlights Intercontinental Exchange, CME Group, Nasdaq and Cboe Global Markets
summary: ICE, CME, Nasdaq and Cboe ride crypto gains, M&A momentum and tech upgrades as trading volumes and non-trading revenues drive strong growth.
